
[1]hyssop

   HYSSOP, n. hy'sop. [L. hyssopus; Gr. It would be well to write this
   word hysop.] A plant or genus of plants, one species of which is
   cultivated for use. The leaves have an aromatic smell, and a warm
   pungent taste. Hyssop was much used by the Jews in purification.
